OSUN State Governor, Mr Adegboyega Oyetola, has said his administration will continue to execute projects based on the needs and demands of the populace. Oyetola spoke through his Special Adviser on Civic Engagement, Mr Olatunbosun Oyintiloye, during a rural community engagement organised by the Civic Engagement Office in the Coker/Boredun area of the state. The governor, while noting that participatory and inclusive governance remained the best path towards socioeconomic and political development, added that his administration placed high premium on people’s contributions to governance. He said, “Participatory and people-oriented administration create a platform for broad socio-political excellence as it facilitates equity and inclusiveness in the art of governance. “That underscores the essence of carrying people along in the state development engineering. The government will continue to listen to the populace, aggregate their needs and always strive to meet them.” According to him, many initiatives of his administration; such as the construction of Olaiya flyover, intercommunity access roads, education policy review and security upgrade among others, were conceived and implemented based on  people’s demand. He  called on the residents to further engage the government regarding the areas of need and not to renege in supporting his administration for more life-changing projects to be conceived and executed. A statement on Saturday by Oyintiloye said the Olu of Coker, Oba Adebare Fadare, while speaking at the meeting, commended Oyetola for “providing purposeful leadership which has made the people the centrepiece of the administration.’’ Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com